00:00:16.149 --> 00:00:17.017  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Nagai] <i>Sato!</i>

2
00:00:18.018 --> 00:00:24.524  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
All of us... we're sick of being
a part of your games!

3
00:00:25.291 --> 00:00:28.395  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
In other words, we're going to take
the nerve gas that was recovered

4
00:00:28.461 --> 00:00:30.764  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and disperse it underground,
thus disabling Sato?

5
00:00:31.031 --> 00:00:36.036  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We can't evacuate the civilians,
or Sato will realize what we're doing.

6
00:00:36.102 --> 00:00:37.504  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We have roughly four hours left.

7
00:00:37.570 --> 00:00:40.273  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Capture Sato before then,
no matter what it takes.

8
00:00:40.340 --> 00:00:41.508  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Go, Ghost!

9
00:00:41.574 --> 00:00:44.711  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Stop them with all you've got!
-I know!

10
00:00:44.778 --> 00:00:47.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Tosaki] He's no revolutionary,
no tactician.

11
00:00:47.547 --> 00:00:49.215  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's just playing a game.

12
00:00:49.282 --> 00:00:52.051  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But that's why he's got a weakness
we can capitalize on.

13
00:00:52.118 --> 00:00:53.186  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What do you plan to do?

14
00:00:54.087 --> 00:00:55.255  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Bury him alive.

15
00:00:56.689 --> 00:00:58.625  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Sato] Nice idea.

16
00:00:59.659 --> 00:01:03.196  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
However... just when you think
you've won...

17
00:01:03.763 --> 00:01:06.733  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
somebody pulls the rug out
from under you.

18
00:01:07.400 --> 00:01:08.268  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What is it?

19
00:01:09.202 --> 00:01:10.737  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-It's going to collapse?
-We overdid it!

20
00:01:10.804 --> 00:01:12.405  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, it's the floor!

21
00:01:12.472 --> 00:01:13.339  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Tosaki!

22
00:01:20.580 --> 00:01:23.550  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Sato] I am going to kill...

23
00:01:24.517 --> 00:01:26.252  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
each and every one of you.

24
00:01:28.354 --> 00:01:29.722  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, we didn't get him?

25
00:01:31.524 --> 00:01:34.694  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Press start to play.

26
00:01:45.371 --> 00:01:48.274  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[chorus singing] <i>Open your eyes</i>
<i>This destiny</i>

27
00:01:48.341 --> 00:01:51.377  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>If I can't escape it</i>

28
00:01:51.444 --> 00:01:53.179  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Then I'll swallow it all down</i>

29
00:01:53.246 --> 00:01:57.484  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Both right and wrong</i>
<i>And I'll fight</i>

30
00:01:57.550 --> 00:01:59.152  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
AJIN: DEMI-HUMAN

31
00:02:04.190 --> 00:02:07.193  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>The menace that dominates</i>

32
00:02:07.260 --> 00:02:10.296  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>The darkness in my troubled mind</i>

33
00:02:10.363 --> 00:02:13.433  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>The truth of a human</i>

34
00:02:13.500 --> 00:02:16.436  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Who has begun to lose control</i>

35
00:02:16.503 --> 00:02:18.738  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>That meaninglessness</i>

36
00:02:18.805 --> 00:02:22.308  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I've come to know it</i>

37
00:02:22.675 --> 00:02:25.178  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>If even counterfeit peace</i>

38
00:02:25.245 --> 00:02:28.748  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Will break into pieces</i>

39
00:02:28.815 --> 00:02:33.386  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I will cast</i>

40
00:02:33.453 --> 00:02:40.293  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>A defiant shadow</i>

41
00:02:41.161 --> 00:02:44.164  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>It's the end of escape</i>
<i>Stand up</i>

42
00:02:44.230 --> 00:02:47.233  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>Because it's the only way</i>

43
00:02:47.300 --> 00:02:53.406  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Follow it</i>
<i>The small hope I aim for</i>

44
00:02:53.473 --> 00:02:56.476  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>The weakness that spilled</i>
<i>From the proffered hand</i>

45
00:02:56.543 --> 00:02:59.679  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I swallowed it all down</i>

46
00:02:59.746 --> 00:03:06.352  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Both right and wrong</i>
<i>And lost my mind</i>

47
00:03:10.490 --> 00:03:14.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'LL MAKE YOU A PROMISE TOO, MR. SATO

48
00:03:16.596 --> 00:03:17.830  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Nagai] What is this place?

49
00:03:21.601 --> 00:03:22.702  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

50
00:03:26.306 --> 00:03:27.607  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Nakano] Nagai!

51
00:03:27.674 --> 00:03:28.708  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nagai!

52
00:03:29.609 --> 00:03:31.544  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What happened?! Search team!

53
00:03:32.478 --> 00:03:33.513  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>An explosion!</i>

54
00:03:33.580 --> 00:03:37.450  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's been a large-scale collapse
caused by an explosion at point F-2!

55
00:03:37.517 --> 00:03:40.787  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's apparently an older underground
bunker beneath the sewers!

56
00:03:40.853 --> 00:03:42.288  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[shouting]

57
00:03:43.790 --> 00:03:45.658  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Damn it, can't reach Okuyama
and the others.

58
00:03:45.992 --> 00:03:47.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nagai!

59
00:03:47.727 --> 00:03:48.928  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nakano, shut up!

60
00:03:51.364 --> 00:03:52.765  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Nagai.
-Where's Sato?!

61
00:03:52.832 --> 00:03:54.867  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Not here! Neither are Izumi
and the others!

62
00:03:55.568 --> 00:03:57.237  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That way's a dead end.

63
00:03:57.303 --> 00:03:58.404  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's going on?

64
00:03:58.471 --> 00:03:59.806  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damn it!

65
00:03:59.872 --> 00:04:01.274  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He got us.

66
00:04:02.342 --> 00:04:04.611  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, we got buried ourselves?

67
00:04:04.677 --> 00:04:06.312  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now the problem is Sato.

68
00:04:06.746 --> 00:04:10.683  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He's sure to come to finish us off,
if he's not trapped.

69
00:04:11.251 --> 00:04:12.452  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gunshots nearby]

70
00:04:12.952 --> 00:04:14.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Is it Sato?
-Must be!

71
00:04:14.587 --> 00:04:17.790  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-So, he must be fighting against Tosaki--
-Izumi!

72
00:04:17.857 --> 00:04:18.758  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's go!

73
00:04:21.427 --> 00:04:23.263  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kuro-chan, please!

74
00:04:28.434 --> 00:04:31.437  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I like to take care of my things.

75
00:04:31.504 --> 00:04:32.772  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The one from before...?!

76
00:04:41.047 --> 00:04:41.948  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Tosaki.

77
00:04:45.618 --> 00:04:46.886  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That won't do.

78
00:04:53.926 --> 00:04:55.928  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Any casualties?
-No, sir.

79
00:04:55.995 --> 00:04:56.863  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's a trap.

80
00:04:56.929 --> 00:04:58.665  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Will this affect the gas deployment?

81
00:04:58.731 --> 00:05:01.901  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Conditions have changed slightly,
but we're still within projections.

82
00:05:01.968 --> 00:05:04.937  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Right. Once the installation is complete,
withdraw immediately!

83
00:05:05.004 --> 00:05:05.872  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Roger!</i>

84
00:05:08.074 --> 00:05:09.909  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We'll retreat as well in five minutes.

85
00:05:15.381 --> 00:05:18.618  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I never thought I'd be your luggage.

86
00:05:19.519 --> 00:05:20.787  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't worry about it.

87
00:05:21.054 --> 00:05:22.488  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is my job--

88
00:05:24.457 --> 00:05:26.693  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll start with you two.

89
00:05:28.594 --> 00:05:31.898  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Izumi] Nagai, can you hear me?! Nagai!

90
00:05:33.966 --> 00:05:39.939  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're going to wish you'd died
before you got in my way.

91
00:05:40.773 --> 00:05:41.974  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gunshot]

92
00:05:43.876 --> 00:05:44.944  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Go!

93
00:05:46.446 --> 00:05:47.113  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hurry!

94
00:06:01.828 --> 00:06:03.696  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's one down.

95
00:06:05.932 --> 00:06:06.833  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What?

96
00:06:11.871 --> 00:06:14.407  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're human, aren't you?

97
00:06:15.808 --> 00:06:17.076  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm a ghost.

98
00:06:17.844 --> 00:06:22.482  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I should have died...
back at the Musashi Building.

99
00:06:23.783 --> 00:06:24.784  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[explosion]

100
00:06:24.951 --> 00:06:26.052  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

101
00:06:34.127 --> 00:06:34.994  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Turn right!

102
00:06:37.597 --> 00:06:40.466  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Three targets confirmed!
It's the Ajin! Capture all of them!

103
00:06:47.140 --> 00:06:48.841  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You kids go on ahead!

104
00:06:57.917 --> 00:06:59.719  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't give up, Mr. Tosaki!

105
00:07:01.087 --> 00:07:02.054  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The bank...

106
00:07:05.424 --> 00:07:06.926  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The safe-deposit box...

107
00:07:07.593 --> 00:07:09.695  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's proof that you're an Ajin.

108
00:07:10.730 --> 00:07:12.765  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Tosaki, what are you talking--?

109
00:07:12.832 --> 00:07:13.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Shut up and listen.

110
00:07:16.436 --> 00:07:19.772  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The key to the safe-deposit box is in
my fiancée's hospital room.

111
00:07:22.875 --> 00:07:23.743  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, go and get it.

112
00:07:24.977 --> 00:07:27.947  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
With this leg, I'll never get away.

113
00:07:28.915 --> 00:07:31.484  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But I'm sure Nagai and the others--

114
00:07:33.219 --> 00:07:34.754  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm ending our contract.

115
00:07:35.755 --> 00:07:38.958  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hurry up and get out of my sight!

116
00:07:41.127 --> 00:07:42.762  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

117
00:07:49.602 --> 00:07:53.005  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you saying I'm free?

118
00:07:53.206 --> 00:07:54.073  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah.

119
00:07:55.475 --> 00:07:56.843  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Go live however you want.

120
00:07:57.109 --> 00:08:00.913  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Izumi] Then I'm free to protect you, too,
right, Mr. Tosaki?

121
00:08:01.547 --> 00:08:04.016  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Don't be so stupid--
-I'm not accepting orders anymore.

122
00:08:04.584 --> 00:08:06.018  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You ended the contract.

123
00:08:06.085 --> 00:08:07.086  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gun clicks]

124
00:08:09.088 --> 00:08:09.956  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Tosaki...

125
00:08:11.891 --> 00:08:15.127  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you for giving me a new life.

126
00:08:15.194 --> 00:08:16.996  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Stop! You can't win!

127
00:08:23.536 --> 00:08:25.104  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, you'll be number two.

128
00:08:29.642 --> 00:08:30.910  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Izumi] <i>Still no good, huh?</i>

129
00:08:41.954 --> 00:08:43.189  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No!

130
00:08:48.694 --> 00:08:52.899  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'll bring you face-to-face
with the new you...

131
00:08:53.199 --> 00:08:54.867  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[shouting then thud]

132
00:08:56.736 --> 00:08:57.670  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm Nagai.

133
00:09:03.976 --> 00:09:05.044  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunts]

134
00:09:08.748 --> 00:09:14.587  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is the end of your games, Mr. Sato!

135
00:09:29.168 --> 00:09:31.737  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're late.

136
00:09:32.338 --> 00:09:34.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[ghost] Sorry about that.

137
00:09:35.808 --> 00:09:39.278  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I must have taken a wrong turn.

138
00:09:58.798 --> 00:10:00.099  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Colonel! This way!

139
00:10:04.971 --> 00:10:06.839  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-And the installation?
-It's finished.

140
00:10:07.273 --> 00:10:09.375  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Right, wait for orders.

141
00:10:13.179 --> 00:10:14.046  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damn it!

142
00:10:18.217 --> 00:10:22.221  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is payback for before!

143
00:10:26.092 --> 00:10:27.059  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You!

144
00:10:29.195 --> 00:10:30.129  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damn it!

145
00:10:34.734 --> 00:10:35.635  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kuro-chan!

146
00:10:38.738 --> 00:10:44.343  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You... I need to return the favor
for our last meeting.

147
00:10:46.112 --> 00:10:49.215  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, then, Tanaka,
I'll leave them to you.

148
00:10:49.281 --> 00:10:50.816  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Got it.

149
00:10:56.355 --> 00:10:59.291  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's one thing
I'd like to ask you, Nagai.

150
00:11:00.059 --> 00:11:02.862  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why do you keep getting in my way?

151
00:11:04.263 --> 00:11:05.998  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Isn't it obvious?

152
00:11:06.766 --> 00:11:12.304  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
As long as you're around,
I'll never be able to live a quiet life.

153
00:11:13.372 --> 00:11:16.175  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're just like me.

154
00:11:16.742 --> 00:11:21.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'd rather you didn't lump me in
with insane people like you.

155
00:11:22.915 --> 00:11:24.350  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do it, Ghost!

156
00:11:38.697 --> 00:11:40.699  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, we're the same.

157
00:11:40.766 --> 00:11:42.802  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You want to live a quiet life.

158
00:11:42.868 --> 00:11:45.337  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I want to play games
to my heart's content.

159
00:11:45.404 --> 00:11:49.008  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But this world won't allow that.

160
00:11:51.844 --> 00:11:53.879  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just one more time!

161
00:11:53.946 --> 00:11:55.347  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ghost!

162
00:12:02.354 --> 00:12:06.325  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, we're both doing what we need to do.

163
00:12:07.193 --> 00:12:08.761  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

164
00:12:18.971 --> 00:12:23.075  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Even you aren't indestructible, Nagai.

165
00:12:23.776 --> 00:12:24.743  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kuro-chan!

166
00:12:33.819 --> 00:12:36.822  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's a question of who has
more real battle experience.

167
00:12:37.389 --> 00:12:38.891  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damn it...

168
00:12:41.193 --> 00:12:42.094  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm.

169
00:12:43.896 --> 00:12:45.231  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[screaming]

170
00:12:49.135 --> 00:12:50.870  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Pathetic.

171
00:12:53.272 --> 00:12:57.543  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Get away from... Izumi...

172
00:12:59.044 --> 00:13:02.781  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This is for what you did
back at the hospital.

173
00:13:09.522 --> 00:13:13.159  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Nagai] Get... away...

174
00:13:13.225 --> 00:13:16.996  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
from... Ms... Izumi.

175
00:13:17.062 --> 00:13:21.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What, you too...?

176
00:13:23.202 --> 00:13:25.237  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't get in my way--

177
00:13:27.173 --> 00:13:28.207  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah?

178
00:13:29.875 --> 00:13:31.310  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[panting]

179
00:13:33.445 --> 00:13:34.914  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

180
00:13:38.417 --> 00:13:39.885  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Less than five minutes left.

181
00:13:40.819 --> 00:13:41.820  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Release the key lock.

182
00:13:42.354 --> 00:13:44.023  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Colonel! It's Sato!

183
00:13:44.089 --> 00:13:45.391  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We've found Sato!

184
00:13:47.826 --> 00:13:48.861  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Colonel...

185
00:13:50.129 --> 00:13:51.931  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Our orders are to use the method

186
00:13:51.997 --> 00:13:55.167  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
with the highest probability of success
in capturing him.

187
00:14:03.008 --> 00:14:04.143  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasping]

188
00:14:07.913 --> 00:14:11.417  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Do you remember the promise
I made you at the lab, Nagai?

189
00:14:12.384 --> 00:14:15.621  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I swore I'd cut off your head.

190
00:14:16.322 --> 00:14:19.925  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll be following through on that now.

191
00:14:22.394 --> 00:14:25.865  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll hold up your severed head...

192
00:14:26.465 --> 00:14:29.401  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and give you a good view
as your new head is generated...

193
00:14:29.468 --> 00:14:32.338  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
right up until you die.

194
00:14:33.005 --> 00:14:35.608  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You won't be you anymore.

195
00:14:38.110 --> 00:14:39.144  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And then...

196
00:14:40.045 --> 00:14:44.483  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I promise to give the new you
a really great show.

197
00:14:45.251 --> 00:14:48.053  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll start with little Eriko.

198
00:14:48.454 --> 00:14:51.223  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Next will be Kaito and your parents.

199
00:14:51.290 --> 00:14:55.895  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then Tosaki, Shimomura, Nakano...

200
00:14:56.328 --> 00:15:00.065  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll kill them all in front of your eyes.

201
00:15:00.332 --> 00:15:02.935  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just like I did at Musashi Industries.

202
00:15:04.670 --> 00:15:06.105  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That...

203
00:15:07.006 --> 00:15:10.676  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
is your punishment for getting in my way.

204
00:15:18.417 --> 00:15:19.285  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

205
00:15:22.121 --> 00:15:22.988  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm...

206
00:15:25.524 --> 00:15:28.460  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll make you a promise too, Mr. Sato.

207
00:15:31.130 --> 00:15:33.299  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No matter where you go...

208
00:15:34.333 --> 00:15:37.236  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I swear I'll find you and kill you.

209
00:15:40.072 --> 00:15:41.173  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is goodbye,

210
00:15:42.041 --> 00:15:43.542  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nagai!

211
00:15:43.609 --> 00:15:45.377  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Nagai!
-Nagai!

212
00:15:45.444 --> 00:15:46.578  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gunshot]

213
00:15:49.982 --> 00:15:51.150  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gunshot]

214
00:15:59.491 --> 00:16:02.594  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[ghosts] I shouldn't try
to save people after all.

215
00:16:02.661 --> 00:16:04.463  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We'll work with you!

216
00:16:04.530 --> 00:16:06.231  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That was on purpose.

217
00:16:06.298 --> 00:16:08.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I won't do it.

218
00:16:08.467 --> 00:16:10.035  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just hurry up.

219
00:16:10.102 --> 00:16:13.539  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Shut up. I'll say it once more.

220
00:16:13.605 --> 00:16:14.673  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Sato.

221
00:16:17.276 --> 00:16:19.511  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sorry to have caused you so much trouble.

222
00:16:22.581 --> 00:16:24.049  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It couldn't be helped.

223
00:16:24.116 --> 00:16:25.050  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He was sick.

224
00:16:27.286 --> 00:16:28.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've gotta pee.

225
00:16:28.387 --> 00:16:31.190  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No! Do you understand
a person's pain?

226
00:16:31.256 --> 00:16:33.258  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's my line.

227
00:16:33.559 --> 00:16:36.595  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm a worthless human being.

228
00:16:36.662 --> 00:16:38.364  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A flood phenomenon...

229
00:16:39.665 --> 00:16:40.733  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[ghosts]
How many more IBMs can you summon?

230
00:16:41.000 --> 00:16:43.035  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You can wait all you want,
but the U.S. military won't be coming.

231
00:16:43.102 --> 00:16:45.404  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll find you and kill you.

232
00:16:45.471 --> 00:16:49.141  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I was only hanging out with him
'cause the poor guy was all alone, anyway.

233
00:17:27.713 --> 00:17:29.681  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey, Nagai--

234
00:17:39.091 --> 00:17:40.325  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Go, go, go!

235
00:17:51.703 --> 00:17:53.205  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't move!

236
00:17:53.272 --> 00:17:55.741  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, wait, I--

237
00:17:55.808 --> 00:17:57.543  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You've got the wrong guy!

238
00:17:58.710 --> 00:17:59.645  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Wait!

239
00:18:02.681 --> 00:18:05.584  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Those Ajin are under the custody
of the Japanese government.

240
00:18:06.585 --> 00:18:09.288  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And that woman is a human
and my subordinate.

241
00:18:09.655 --> 00:18:11.090  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

242
00:18:11.690 --> 00:18:13.258  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sato and Tanaka.

243
00:18:13.592 --> 00:18:16.528  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I believe that was the agreement.

244
00:18:22.768 --> 00:18:23.669  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Move out.

245
00:18:36.615 --> 00:18:40.686  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The Americans thought better
of using the gas at the last minute.

246
00:18:40.752 --> 00:18:42.621  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Sokabe] You should be grateful
to Mr. Tosaki.

247
00:18:43.122 --> 00:18:46.625  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Your presence will be overlooked
in return for stopping Sato.

248
00:18:47.526 --> 00:18:50.262  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He insisted on those absurd terms.

249
00:18:50.562 --> 00:18:51.497  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Tosaki...

250
00:18:54.500 --> 00:18:57.402  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't forget about pardoning me as well.

251
00:19:23.929 --> 00:19:29.401  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>A new Ajin protection bill has been</i>
<i>agreed upon by the cabinet this afternoon.</i>

252
00:19:30.369 --> 00:19:33.739  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Once the Diet deliberates,</i>
<i>the bill, which will see civil rights</i>

253
00:19:33.805 --> 00:19:37.709  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>extended to Ajin in actuality as well</i>
<i>as in name, is expected to pass.</i>

254
00:19:38.844 --> 00:19:41.380  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>It seems</i>
<i>that the violence perpetrated by...</i>

255
00:19:41.446 --> 00:19:44.283  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[woman] Ms. Nagai,
it's time to take a blood sample.

256
00:19:46.485 --> 00:19:48.854  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, you saw your brother again.

257
00:19:49.454 --> 00:19:51.590  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-It's so nice that you two are so close.
-Yes.

258
00:19:51.823 --> 00:19:55.327  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No, I mean,
we're not really all that close...

259
00:19:57.262 --> 00:19:58.697  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's just what I said to him!

260
00:19:58.764 --> 00:20:00.432  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Whoa, way to go!

261
00:20:00.499 --> 00:20:02.634  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That is just too crazy.

262
00:20:03.202 --> 00:20:05.704  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Right?
-It's, like, totally hilarious!

263
00:20:23.822 --> 00:20:24.890  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[cell phone buzzing]

264
00:20:28.527 --> 00:20:29.461  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm?

265
00:20:31.730 --> 00:20:32.698  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes...

266
00:20:34.733 --> 00:20:36.301  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's been a while.

267
00:20:37.436 --> 00:20:38.570  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's going on?

268
00:20:40.505 --> 00:20:41.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Huh?

269
00:20:48.780 --> 00:20:50.682  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Go! Go! Go!

270
00:21:07.666 --> 00:21:09.601  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] I can't believe he's real.

271
00:21:10.469 --> 00:21:12.971  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah, well, I still can't believe it.

272
00:21:13.038 --> 00:21:14.906  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's a human who can't die, man.

273
00:21:14.973 --> 00:21:16.875  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How does that work?

274
00:21:17.442 --> 00:21:18.377  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Right?

275
00:21:19.044 --> 00:21:21.747  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yeah, it's like something
out of a video game.

276
00:21:22.781 --> 00:21:26.418  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You could have a lot of fun
with a body like that.

277
00:21:32.624 --> 00:21:36.428  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I haven't dreamed like that in ages.

278
00:21:36.495 --> 00:21:39.431  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I can't believe you can sleep so soundly.

279
00:21:39.498 --> 00:21:42.334  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We have no idea
what they'll do to us now...

280
00:21:42.401 --> 00:21:44.069  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are you saying?

281
00:21:44.736 --> 00:21:47.773  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This is just the beginning
of the second play-through.

282
00:21:48.440 --> 00:21:50.909  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And how would we...?

283
00:21:51.543 --> 00:21:52.511  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[electronic beeping]

284
00:21:53.879 --> 00:21:58.450  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I love it
when a plan comes together, Tanabe.

285
00:21:58.517 --> 00:21:59.618  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Huh?

286
00:22:12.631 --> 00:22:14.466  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
When did this happen?

287
00:22:14.533 --> 00:22:16.868  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Tosaki over phone]
